# Restructure Portfolio Website into Organized Folders

The monolithic `Personal Portfolio Website.html` (1504 lines) has all CSS, HTML, and JS inline. This plan separates it into a clean, maintainable folder structure.

## Proposed Folder Structure

```
portfolio/
├── index.html                    # Clean HTML structure only
├── css/
│   ├── variables.css             # CSS custom properties & resets
│   ├── layout.css                # Container, nav, section, footer layout
│   ├── hero.css                  # Hero section styles
│   ├── about.css                 # About section styles
│   ├── skills.css                # Skills grid & card styles
│   ├── projects.css              # Projects grid & card styles
│   ├── contact.css               # Contact form & info styles
│   ├── animations.css            # All @keyframes & scroll-reveal
│   └── responsive.css            # All @media queries
├── js/
│   ├── navigation.js             # Smooth scroll & active nav state
│   ├── form.js                   # Contact form submission handler
│   ├── animations.js             # Scroll reveal, parallax, cursor trail
│   └── cards.js                  # Skill card mouse tracking effect
└── assets/
    └── (empty — placeholder for future images/fonts)
```

